{"title":"How to watch the Tour de France 2024","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-tour-de-france","date":1719235873000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-the-tour-de-france\">How to watch the Tour de France 2024</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s back. The 2024 Tour de France begins on Saturday 29th June in Florence, Italy. Defending champion<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/jonas-vingegaard\" target=\"_blank\"> Jonas Vingegaard</a> (Visma-Lease a Bike) will line up alongside two-time winner <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tadej-pogacar\" target=\"_blank\">Tadej Pogačar</a> (UAE Team Emirates) in the fight for the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/in-celebration-of-the-yellow-jersey\" target=\"_blank\">yellow jersey</a>. They will be joined by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/primoz-roglic\" target=\"_blank\">Primož Roglič</a> (Red Bull-Bora-Hansgrohe) and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel</a> (Soudal-QuickStep) in what is a <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-2024-underdogs\" target=\"_blank\">stacked field of title contenders</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The peloton will spend the first three (and a half) days in Italy. The iconic <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/galibier-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">Col du Galibier</a> features as early as Stage 4 when the race enters the mountains early on. A move northwards sees the riders take on a time-trial through wine country on Stage 8 and a gravel stage around Troyes on Stage 9. The Tour will then gear up for the Pyrenees with two summit finishes on stages 14 and 15. The final week is mountainous and challenging through <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-climbs\" target=\"_blank\">the Maritime Alps</a>. Instead of reaching Paris, the Tour concludes in Nice this year with an up and down time-trial from Monaco.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are plenty of storylines to follow at the 2024 Tour de France. Keep an eye out for <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/mark-cavendish\" target=\"_blank\">Mark Cavendish</a> looking to break the stage win record he currently shares with Eddy Merckx, UAE Team Emirates’s hefty roster and Jonas Vingegaard’s comeback from injury.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-2024-underdogs\">Who actually are the underdogs for the Tour de France?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-climbs\">The climbs that will decide the 2024 Tour de France</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-tour-double\">What does it take to win the Giro-Tour double?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-do-tour-de-france-favourites-prepare\">How are the favourites preparing for the Tour de France?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-de-france-route-live-tv-guide-startlist-stage-by-stage\">Men’s Tour de France 2024: Route, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch and live stream the Tour de France 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-970x647.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-63.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Hervé Tarrieu</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As always, live coverage of the 2024 Tour de France in the UK is on ITV4, S4C, Discovery+ and Eurosport.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Eurosport and ITV4 will be providing extensive live coverage of all 21 stages as well as evening highlights. In the UK, ITV4 is a free-to-air channel and will be available on all UK television packages. Additionally, the racing can be seen live online on <a href=\"https://www.itv.com/watch?channel=itv4\" target=\"_blank\">ITVX</a>, which is also free. Welsh language coverage is also broadcast on free-to-air channel S4C throughout the UK.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The other option is streaming. The Eurosport coverage is streamed via <a href=\"https://www.discoveryplus.com/gb\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a>, which offers uninterrupted live coverage, including Eurosport’s ‘The Breakaway’ headed up by <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/orla-chennaoui-interview\" target=\"_blank\">Orla Chennaoui</a>. <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">A Discovery+ subscription</a> currently costs £6.99 per month with the basic package, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the United States, the racing will be broadcast on NBC Sports and its streaming service Peacock. Australia offers coverage via SBS Sports, and FloBikes holds the broadcast rights for English-speaking Canada. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country, you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while abroad in countries without access.  </p>\n\n\n\n<p>One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find a way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month, with three months free. Other options include <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fnordvpn.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">NordVPN</a>, <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsurfshark.com%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Surfshark</a> and <a href=\"https://go.skimresources.com/?id=205647X1684865&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kaspersky.co.uk%2F\" target=\"_blank\">Kapersky</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Read more: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-cycling\" target=\"_blank\">How to watch cycling post-GCN</a></strong> </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Worldwide broadcasters of the 2024 Tour de France</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-970x647.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-970x646.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-300x200.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-768x512.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-1536x1024.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-750x500.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-1140x760.png 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-465x310.png 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-620x413.png 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67-350x233.png 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/06/file-67.png 1800w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O./Pauline Ballet</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Australia</strong>: SBS<br /><strong>Belgium</strong>: RTBF, VRT<br /><strong>Canada</strong>: FloBikes<br /><strong>China</strong>: CCTV, Zhibo TV<br /><strong>Colombia</strong>: CaracoITV<br /><strong>Czech Republic</strong>: Česká Televize<br /><strong>Denmark</strong>: TV2<br /><strong>Europe</strong>: Eurosport<br /><strong>France</strong>: Eurosport France, France TV Sport<br /><strong>Germany</strong>: ARD, Discovery+<br /><strong>Ireland</strong>: TG4<br /><strong>Italy</strong>: Discovery+, RAI Sport<br /><strong>Japan</strong>: J Sports<br /><strong>Latin America &amp; Caribbean</strong>: ESPN<br /><strong>Luxembourg</strong>: RTL<br /><strong>Middle East &amp; North Africa</strong>: BeIN Sports, TV5 Monde<br /><strong>Netherlands</strong>: Discovery+, NOS<br /><strong>New Zealand</strong>: Sky Sport<br /><strong>Norway</strong>: TV2<br /><strong>Pays Basque</strong>: EiTB<br /><strong>Portugal</strong>: RTP<br /><strong>Scandinavia</strong>: Discovery+<br /><strong>Slovakia</strong>: RTVS<br /><strong>Slovenia</strong>: RTV SLO<br /><strong>Spain</strong>: RTVE<br /><strong>Sub-Saharan Africa</strong>: Supersport<br /><strong>South East Asia</strong>: Eurosport<br /><strong>South America: </strong>TV5 Monde<br /><strong>Switzerland</strong>: SRG-SSR<br /><strong>United Kingdom</strong>: Discovery+, ITV<br /><strong>United States</strong>: NBC Sports, TV5 Monde<br /><strong>Wales</strong>: S4C</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour de France 2024: Live UK TV guide</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"693\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-970x693.jpg\" alt=\"cyclist in white and red raises arms in celebration ahead of group\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-970x693.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-300x214.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-768x549.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-1536x1097.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-2048x1463.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-120x86.jpg 120w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-350x250.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-750x536.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-1140x814.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/07/Tour-de-France-2023-goding-15-190x136.jpg 190w\" /><figcaption>Pete Goding/Goding Images</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Live TV coverage of the 2024 Tour de France is shown on Eurosport, Discovery+, ITV4 and S4C alongside evening highlights. ITV4 also runs one hour highlights shows from every stage at 19:00.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times are subject to change by the broadcasters and listed as BST</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Team Presentation: Thursday 27th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>17:30-19:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>17:30-19:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Saturday 29th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong>Discovery</strong>+: </strong>10:30-17:15<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 10:30-17:15<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-17:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Sunday 30th June</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong><strong>Discovery</strong></strong>+: </strong>11:00-17:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>11:00-17:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>11:15-16:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Monday 1st July</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong><strong>Discovery</strong></strong>+ </strong>10:00-16:45<br /><strong>Eurosport 1:</strong> 10:00-16:45<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>14:00-16:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Tuesday 2nd July</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong><strong>Discovery</strong></strong>+: </strong>11:45-16:45<br /><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>11:30-16:45<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>TBC</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Wednesday 3rd July</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong><strong>Discovery</strong></strong>+ </strong>12:00-17:00<br /><strong>Eurosport 1: </strong>12:00-17:00<br /><strong>ITV4:</strong> TBC</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Thursday 4th July</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><strong><strong>Discovery</strong></strong>+: </strong>11:45-17:00<br /><strong>Eurosport:</strong> 12:00-17:00<br /><str